      "content": "While over-the-counter ear drops can help soften earwax, relying solely on them may not be effective and could delay proper treatment. If you've pushed earwax further into your ear canals, it may take more than a day or two to clear up. In fact, leaving the blockage untreated for an extended period can lead to more serious issues. It's recommended to consult a doctor to get a proper evaluation and treatment plan rather than waiting to see if it resolves on its own.",
